pageContext.claim: “If you look at Hispanic American, Asian American, the best -- the best employment and unemployment numbers in the history of our country. With women, we're at 71 percent. Seventy-one years. Think of this, 71 years. The best numbers in 71 years.”
pageContext.analysis: The Asian-American statistic has been around for less than 20 years. And while it reached a low of 2.0 percent rate in May 2018, it rose to 2.9 percent in August, the most recent month available. Hispanic unemployment has also rebounded. Lately, Trump has been using the word "reached," perhaps to indicate the lows are in the past. As for women's unemployment, it's the lowest in 66 years.
